docs/source/design-system.md:1:# design-system.md
docs/source/design-system.md:3:# SFPCL Member Credit Administration & Settlement — Detailed Design System
docs/source/design-system.md:5:## 1. Document Control
docs/source/design-system.md:16:| Primary process covered | Member loan request, assessment, sanction, documentation, disbursement, monitoring, repayment, default handling, closure and compliance |
docs/source/design-system.md:20:## 2. Purpose of This Design System
docs/source/design-system.md:22:This design system defines the visual, interaction, content, component and implementation standards for the SFPCL Member Credit Administration & Settlement product. It translates the SOP-driven loan lifecycle into a consistent product experience that is usable by operational teams while preserving the strict controls required for member lending, statutory compliance, documentation, finance posting, disbursement, repayment monitoring and auditability.
docs/source/design-system.md:27:2. **No uncontrolled disbursement.** Disbursement must be blocked until sanction, documentation, SAP setup, bank verification and checklist approvals are complete.
docs/source/design-system.md:28:3. **No invisible exceptions.** Any deviation from limits, policy, required documentation or approval sequence must be visibly captured in an Exception Register flow.
docs/source/design-system.md:30:5. **No fragmented information.** Registers, dashboards and operational queues must be views generated from the same underlying loan record, not separate data islands.
docs/source/design-system.md:32:7. **No compliance ambiguity.** Legal and regulatory gates must be surfaced through statuses, warnings, checklists, required reason capture and audit trails.
docs/source/design-system.md:36:## 3. Product Context the Design System Must Support
docs/source/design-system.md:38:### 3.1 Organisation Context
docs/source/design-system.md:42:### 3.2 Process Scope
docs/source/design-system.md:48:| 1 | Initial Loan Request | Application intake, borrower / nominee data, KYC and supporting documents |
docs/source/design-system.md:55:### 3.3 Primary User Roles
docs/source/design-system.md:61:| Borrower / Member / Farmer / FPC | Simple application status, required document guidance, repayment information, NOC / closure communication and grievance access |
docs/source/design-system.md:62:| Deputy Manager – Finance | Application completeness, reference number generation, appraisal drafting, document checks and handoff to Credit Manager |
docs/source/design-system.md:64:| Compliance Team Member | Documentation preparation, checklist management, stamping status, legal document tracking and signature mismatch handling |
docs/source/design-system.md:68:| Senior Manager – Finance | SAP customer code creation coordination, final document verification, disbursement initiation and checklist completion |
docs/source/design-system.md:71:| IT Head / System Administrator | User access, role configuration, data protection, audit logs and system health |
docs/source/design-system.md:72:| Internal / Statutory Auditor | Read-only audit evidence, registers, documents, approvals, logs and exception traceability |
docs/source/design-system.md:76:## 4. Design System Principles
docs/source/design-system.md:78:### 4.1 Compliance First, Usability Always
docs/source/design-system.md:82:### 4.2 Lifecycle-First Navigation
docs/source/design-system.md:86:### 4.3 One Loan, One Source of Truth
docs/source/design-system.md:88:All dashboards, queues and registers must derive from the same canonical loan application / loan account record. The UI should discourage duplicate offline registers by making register views exportable and auditable.
docs/source/design-system.md:90:### 4.4 Maker-Checker by Default
docs/source/design-system.md:92:Any action with financial, legal, compliance or borrower impact should separate preparation from approval. The design system must include reusable maker-checker patterns for appraisal, sanction, documentation, disbursement, recovery and closure.
docs/source/design-system.md:94:### 4.5 Traceability Over Speed
docs/source/design-system.md:96:The product must prioritise complete records, captured reasons and visible evidence over fast but undocumented action.
docs/source/design-system.md:98:### 4.6 No Invisible Business Logic
docs/source/design-system.md:100:Calculations and blockers must be explainable. Loan limit, eligibility, DPD, approval authority and document completeness should display input values and calculation breakdowns.
docs/source/design-system.md:102:### 4.7 Role-Aware but Consistent
docs/source/design-system.md:106:### 4.8 Farmer-Friendly Communication
docs/source/design-system.md:110:### 4.9 Configurable for Policy Changes
docs/source/design-system.md:112:The SOP contains policy values that may change, including share valuation percentage, per-acre cost of cultivation, loan thresholds, interest rate, penal charges and re-KYC frequency. UI components must read these from configuration, not hard-coded copy or logic.
docs/source/design-system.md:114:### 4.10 Audit-Ready by Design
docs/source/design-system.md:116:Every critical component should answer: who acted, when, under what authority, based on which data, with which documents, with what result.
docs/source/design-system.md:120:## 5. Brand and Visual Foundations
docs/source/design-system.md:122:### 5.1 Brand Attributes
docs/source/design-system.md:129:| Transparency | Visible calculations, audit trails, status explanations and non-hidden blockers |
docs/source/design-system.md:132:| Compliance | Formal states, document completeness patterns, mandatory reason capture |
docs/source/design-system.md:135:### 5.2 Logo and Brand Asset Usage
docs/source/design-system.md:143:| Generated documents | Full-width header logo with company name and document metadata |
docs/source/design-system.md:144:| Borrower communication PDFs | Logo plus contact information and document title |
docs/source/design-system.md:151:- Do not place the logo on low-contrast or busy backgrounds.
docs/source/design-system.md:153:- Do not embed unofficial watermarks in legal documents.
docs/source/design-system.md:155:### 5.3 Visual Tone
