docs/source/api-contracts.md:4282:# 50. Final API Contract Summary
docs/source/api-contracts.md:4284:The SFPCL API architecture must support a strict, auditable and workflow-driven lending lifecycle. The API should not expose generic CRUD alone. It must expose explicit, permission-controlled action endpoints that correspond to the SOP controls:
docs/source/api-contracts.md:4293:- Generate and verify documents.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:1:# Implementation Roadmap — SFPCL Member Credit Administration & Loan Disbursement Platform
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:3:## 1. Document Control
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:21:## 2. Purpose
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:23:This document defines a detailed implementation roadmap for building and launching the SFPCL Member Credit Administration & Loan Disbursement Platform.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:41:The roadmap is designed for a workflow-heavy, compliance-sensitive internal lending platform, not a generic CRUD application. It therefore prioritises controls, auditability and lifecycle gates before optional automation.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:45:## 3. Strategic Product Goal
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:50:- KYC and document control.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:55:- Legal documentation and security instruments.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:62:- Statutory compliance trackers and audit evidence.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:67:SFPCL staff can process member credit from initial request to closure through a secure, auditable, role-based workflow that enforces SOP gates and prevents disbursement or recovery actions unless all required approvals, documents, security instruments and evidence are complete.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:72:## 4. Roadmap Principles
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:76:| Controls before convenience | Build workflow gates, RBAC, audit and validations before optional automation. |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:79:| State-machine discipline | Loan applications, approvals, documents, disbursements, repayments, defaults and closures must move through controlled states. |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:80:| Security by default | Sensitive data must be encrypted, masked and audit-controlled from the first release. |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:82:| Incremental business value | Release usable stages in phases, starting with origination and approvals, then documentation/disbursement, then servicing/compliance. |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:83:| Audit-ready by design | Critical actions should leave evidence: who, when, role, reason, old value, new value and related document. |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:89:# 5. Scope Baseline
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:91:## 5.1 MVP Scope
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:105:| KYC document upload and verification | Yes |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:119:| Legal document generation | Yes |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:150:| Compliance dashboards | Yes |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:161:## 5.2 Non-MVP / Future Scope
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:175:| AI document extraction | Not needed for initial controlled workflow. |
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:179:# 6. Roadmap Overview
