docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2319:# 36. Final Implementation Roadmap Summary
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2323:1. **Build the secure foundation first**: authentication, RBAC, audit, documents, configuration and deployment.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2326:4. **Add legal/documentation controls**: templates, signatures, stamp duty, notarisation, checklist and security instruments.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2336:Do not automate external systems before the internal workflow controls are correct. First make every SOP gate, approval, document, security instrument, disbursement, repayment and audit record reliable inside the platform; then replace manual external steps with API integrations where business value and provider readiness justify it.
docs/source/content-spec.md:1:# content-spec.md
docs/source/content-spec.md:2:# SFPCL Member Credit Administration & Settlement — Detailed Content Specification
docs/source/content-spec.md:4:## 1. Document Control
docs/source/content-spec.md:11:| Process basis | Member credit administration, loan sanction, documentation, disbursement, repayment, monitoring, settlement and compliance |
docs/source/content-spec.md:14:| Document purpose | Define all product content, naming, labels, messages, helper text, notifications, document copy, report labels, workflow copy and governance rules required to implement the system consistently |
docs/source/content-spec.md:20:## 2. Purpose of This Content Specification
docs/source/content-spec.md:22:This document defines the content layer for the SFPCL Member Credit Administration & Settlement system. It translates the SOP-driven process into a controlled content system covering:
docs/source/content-spec.md:32:- Notifications, reminders, emails and SMS messages.
docs/source/content-spec.md:33:- Generated document and template content.
docs/source/content-spec.md:39:The goal is to make the product clear, compliant, auditable and easy to operate across Credit Assessment, Compliance, Treasury, Accounts, Sanction Committee, CFO, Directors, CFC, auditors and borrowers.
docs/source/content-spec.md:43:## 3. Content Strategy Summary
docs/source/content-spec.md:47:1. **Lifecycle clarity** — every loan must visibly move through request, assessment, sanction, documentation, disbursement, repayment, monitoring, default handling and closure.
docs/source/content-spec.md:48:2. **Control-first language** — content should make approval gates, documentation blockers and compliance requirements explicit.
docs/source/content-spec.md:51:5. **Audit-ready wording** — system-generated content should produce a clear evidence trail suitable for internal audit, statutory audit and Board review.
docs/source/content-spec.md:54:8. **Documented ambiguity** — unresolved SOP contradictions must be surfaced as configuration / policy confirmation items, not silently hardcoded.
docs/source/content-spec.md:58:## 4. Source Process Summary to Anchor Content
docs/source/content-spec.md:60:### 4.1 Business Context
docs/source/content-spec.md:68:- KYC and document verification before appraisal.
docs/source/content-spec.md:75:- Formal closure with NOC and return of security documents.
docs/source/content-spec.md:77:### 4.2 Six SOP Stages
docs/source/content-spec.md:90:### 4.3 Hard Control Gates to Communicate
docs/source/content-spec.md:98:- Documentation cannot be marked complete unless mandatory documents are verified.
docs/source/content-spec.md:105:## 5. Voice, Tone and Content Style
docs/source/content-spec.md:107:### 5.1 Product Voice
docs/source/content-spec.md:118:### 5.2 Tone by Context
docs/source/content-spec.md:127:| Default handling | Neutral, documented and non-coercive | “Record reason for non-payment and classify whether it is intentional or non-intentional.” |
docs/source/content-spec.md:130:### 5.3 Writing Rules
docs/source/content-spec.md:135:- Title case only for formal document names, registers and legal forms.
docs/source/content-spec.md:140:- “Nominee” for the person signing application and related documentation.
docs/source/content-spec.md:141:- “Witness” only for document execution witness.
docs/source/content-spec.md:151:### 5.4 Mandatory Reason Capture
docs/source/content-spec.md:171:## 6. Controlled Vocabulary
docs/source/content-spec.md:173:### 6.1 Core Entity Names
docs/source/content-spec.md:186:| Loan Appraisal Note | Credit Assessment recommendation document | Credit memo, CAM unless configured |
docs/source/content-spec.md:189:| Document Checklist | Index and control checklist for loan documents | Document list only |
docs/source/content-spec.md:194:### 6.2 Role Names
docs/source/content-spec.md:202:| Company Secretary | Compliance owner, document verification, stamping and legal documentation |
docs/source/content-spec.md:203:| Compliance Team Member | Prepares documentation set and coordinates checklist |
docs/source/content-spec.md:214:### 6.3 Legal and Compliance Terms
docs/source/content-spec.md:218:| KYC | Identity and address verification using PAN, Aadhaar and other approved documents. |
docs/source/content-spec.md:221:| 7/12 extract | Land record document used to verify agricultural land details. |
docs/source/content-spec.md:233:## 7. Formatting Standards
docs/source/content-spec.md:235:### 7.1 Currency
docs/source/content-spec.md:249:### 7.2 Dates
docs/source/content-spec.md:275:### 7.3 IDs and Reference Numbers
docs/source/content-spec.md:291:### 7.4 Percentages
docs/source/content-spec.md:300:### 7.5 Names
docs/source/content-spec.md:302:Use full legal name in formal documents. Use shorter display name only in dashboard cards.
docs/source/content-spec.md:304:### 7.6 File Names
docs/source/content-spec.md:306:Generated documents should follow a predictable naming pattern:
docs/source/content-spec.md:309:{application_no}_{document_type}_{borrower_name}_{YYYYMMDD}.pdf
